By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  Plateau state on Friday took the lead on the infection table  with 103 cases and  Lagos state, the epicentre of the novel coronavirius came 2nd with 70  patients as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control reported 443 new cases in Nigeria. According to the report released by the health agency via its official  twitter handle,  FCT, Ondo and Edo came 3rd, 4th and 5th with 60, 35 and 27 confirmed cases respectively. The witnessed increase for COVID-19 infections in Ondo and Edo is not unconnected with the political campaigns going on in the two states which has led  to the violation of the NCDC’s COVID-19 recommended protocols of social distancing among others. However, with the new reported cases, Nigeria has recorded a total of 45,687 confirmed cases out of which a total of 32,637 patients have been treated and discharged. Also, the released report has it that 936 deaths have been recorded in the country since the index case that took place on February 27, 2020. The NCDC’s latest report is as shown below: 443 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; Plateau-103Lagos-70FCT-60Ondo-35Edo-27Rivers-27Kaduna-20Osun-19Borno-18Oyo-18Kwara-11Adamawa-9Nasarawa-7Gombe-6Bayelsa-4Imo-4Bauchi-2Ogun-2Kano-1 45,687 confirmed32,637 discharged936 deaths   By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Lagos state, Kwara and Federal Capital Territory top the list of COVID-19 infections on Tuesday as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control confirmed 576 new cases of the dreaded virus in Nigeria. The health agency in its report released via its twitter handle… July 22, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Abujah Racheal ABUJA - The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has recorded 404  new COVID-19 cases in the country, as total infections from the virus rise to 42,208. The NCDC made this known on its official twitter handle on Wednesday. The health agency noted that five more persons… July 30, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Abujah Racheal  ABUJA - A The Nigeria Centre f